gdrive-sync (0.6.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix a serious state-loss bug: if the app started while the GSettings
    schemas were briefly unavailable (typically right after a package
    upgrade), it silently fell back to an empty in-memory configuration,
    opened the setup wizard as if unconfigured, and the wizard could then
    purge the on-disk state of a real account (making it demand a repair).
    The GUI now shows an explanatory error instead, and the daemon refuses
    to start with an empty fallback configuration when accounts exist on
    disk (systemd retries until the schemas are back).
  * The repair dialog now shows a spinner while the preview is computed,
    and a repairing account shows "Realigning…" instead of "First
    synchronization…", so it is clear the repair is actually running.

 -- Stefano Teodorani <stefano.teodorani@horsa.it>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 18:00:00 +0200

gdrive-sync (0.6.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: a brand-new account whose local folder starts out empty failed
    every synchronization with "empty prior Path1 listing" (the manual
    sync button appeared broken and adding a file triggered an error).
    Nothing is tracked in that state, so the engine now realigns
    automatically once — with a guard against loops.
  * New application-wide Preferences dialog (main menu): the tray icon
    and start-at-login options moved there from the per-account
    preferences, together with a Service log viewer.
  * The per-account log now shows only that account's sync log (service
    messages moved to the global dialog).

 -- Stefano Teodorani <stefano.teodorani@horsa.it>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 17:00:00 +0200

