gdrive-sync (0.5.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * System tray icon (StatusNotifierItem, implemented over plain D-Bus in
    the sync daemon): shows the per-account status and offers sync now,
    pause/resume and opening the app. Native on KDE Plasma; on GNOME it
    requires the AppIndicator extension.
  * New "Tray icon" toggle in the preferences (applies to all accounts).

 -- Stefano Teodorani <stefano.teodorani@horsa.it>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 15:00:00 +0200

gdrive-sync (0.4.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: the repair preview (dry-run) ran in the daemon's bisync workdir,
    leaving a lock that made the actual repair — and any concurrent sync —
    fail instantly, so clicking "Repair" appeared to do nothing. The
    preview now uses its own scratch workdir, is cancelled when the dialog
    closes, and never runs twice in parallel.
  * Fix: a missing filters file is now regenerated before every sync run
    with the account's folder selection; previously it was recreated only
    at daemon startup and without the include rules, silently widening the
    sync to the whole Drive and blocking every repair.
  * Removing an account now also deletes the filters hash companion file.

 -- Stefano Teodorani <stefano.teodorani@horsa.it>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 14:00:00 +0200

gdrive-sync (0.4.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * The Drive folder selection can now be changed after setup: the account
    preferences gain a "Synchronized folders" editor with the same checkbox
    tree (and folder sizes) as the wizard, pre-filled with the current
    selection. Applying a change rewrites the rclone filters and starts the
    required realignment (resync) automatically.
  * The daemon now accepts a user-requested resync from the idle and error
    states, not only from needs-resync.

 -- Stefano Teodorani <stefano.teodorani@horsa.it>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 13:00:00 +0200

gdrive-sync (0.4.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: the first synchronization of a new account failed with "filters
    file has changed (must run --resync)" when bisync state from a removed
    account or a previous installation was still on disk. The wizard now
    starts from a clean per-account state, and removing an account also
    deletes its bisync listings, status, log and filters file.

 -- Stefano Teodorani <stefano.teodorani@horsa.it>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

gdrive-sync (0.4.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Setup wizard: the first page now only asks to connect the Google
    account; folder selection moved to its own page.
  * Multiple Drive folders can be selected for synchronization from a
    checkbox tree that also shows the size of each folder (selection is
    applied through rclone filter rules).
  * Multi-language interface: English, French and Italian, chosen
    automatically from the system language.

